Description: Ingot Systems provides design solutions to fabless semiconductor and system companies. The company offers full-chip application-specific
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Ingot Systems provides design solutions to fabless semiconductor and system companies. The company offers full-chip application-specific integrated circuit (ASIC) and system-on-chip (SoC) designs; field programmable gate-array designs; and system designs. It also provides ASIC/SoC design verification services; physical design services; and silicon prototyping/production services. The company, through its subsidiaries, offers its services in the form of various intellectual property (IP) solutions, which include memory controller solutions; and interface solutions that provide flow control, error handling, power management, and hot-plug/hot-swap support. It also provides video solutions, such as video decoder IP cores and video encoder IP cores; networking solutions, including bridge interface cores, switch interconnects cores, and encoder/decoder IP solutions; and Soc IP building blocks. The company operates design centers in Santa Clara, California and Pune, India. Ingot Systems was founded in 2003 and is based in Santa Clara, California. As of August 15, 2007, Ingot Systems, Inc. is a subsidiary of Virage Logic Corporation.

It offers EnCapta technology that provides specialized engineering environments for aero structures development, airframe design and assembly, composites engineering, and seating/interiors design and manufacturing. The company also provides solutions in the areas of automated deposition design, documentation, analysis interface, flat pattern export, laser projection, fiber placement interface, tape laying interface, and composite viewer, as well as airframe design environment, airframe manufacturing environment, and quality planning environment. The company serves various industries, including aerospace and defense, automotive, marine, space, medical equipment, transportation interiors, recreational products, consumer goods, and wind energy. The company has a strategic partnership with Delta Sigma Corporation. VISTAGY, Inc. was formerly known as Composite Design Technologies, Inc. and changed its name to VISTAGY, Inc. in January 2001. The company was founded in 1991 and is based in Waltham, Massachusetts with additional offices in Dallas and Fort Worth, Texas; London, England; Paris, France; Munich and Stuttgart, Germany; Beijing, China; Tokyo, Japan; and Changwon, South Korea.
